Node.js — directly explain karta hoon.

Node.js is a JavaScript runtime built on Chrome's V8 engine. Basically browser ke bahar JavaScript run kar sakte ho — server pe.

```javascript
// server.js
const http = require('http');

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
  res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'text/plain' });
  res.end('Hello from Node.js!');
});

server.listen(3000, () => console.log('Server running on port 3000'));
```

Run karo: `node server.js` — that's it.

Real world mein Express ya Fastify use karte hain directly, but concept yahi hai. Let's build something real — theory baad mein.
